    <thetext>Description of problem:

Hi,

Installed kgamma on Fedora 24 on a year old laptop. 

Modifying the gamma settings functions, but the settings are not saved after the sessions has ended (logout) or the PC rebooted. 

Attempting to save the settings system wide causes the error :

Cannot execute command &apos; xf86gammacfg 0.60 0.60 0.60 &apos;&apos;&apos;.

Logging in, with the settings not implemented, selecting System Settings → Display and Monitor → then the Gamma tab immediately sets the gamma to the value in the settings. 

This is repeatable – logging out and back in resets to default gamma setting, and above implements the saved settings. 

Regards,

Richard. 

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
1.5.8.4-1

How reproducible:
Always reproducible

Steps to Reproduce:
1.Set the gamma in the GUI and apply - notice changes
2.Logout
3.Log back in and settings are not applied. 
4. Select System Setting -&gt; Display and Monitor -&gt; Gamma tab and immediately the settings are applied. 

Actual results:
As per bug report. 

Expected results:
As per bug report 

